Relax the frontend input schema of a compiled rapid-cdn 1.0.469 software release
so a newer master can request its frontend node in a mixed-release cluster
(the master sends parameters, e.g. the error-page-manager options, that landed
after 1.0.469 and that additionalProperties:false would reject).

Applied in place to the already-compiled software release -- whose schema files
sit at the software-release root -- not to the source checkout: this models an
operator hotfixing a deployed release for fast rollback.

--- a/instance-frontend-input-schema.json
+++ b/instance-frontend-input-schema.json
@@ -195,5 +195,5 @@
       "default": 23433
     }
   },
-  "additionalProperties": false
+  "additionalProperties": true
 }
